axiom Person : Type
axiom S : Person → Prop
axiom A : Person → Prop
axiom B : Person → Prop
axiom C : Person → Prop
axiom D : Person → Prop
axiom E : Person → Prop
axiom F : Person → Prop

axiom H : Person

axiom p1 : ∀ x : Person, (S x ∧ A x) → B x
axiom p2 : ∀ x : Person, (S x ∧ C x) → A x
axiom p3 : ∀ x : Person, S x → (C x ∨ D x)
axiom p4 : ∀ x : Person, (S x ∧ D x) → ¬ E x
axiom p5 : ∀ x : Person, (S x ∧ D x) → F x
axiom p6 : S H
axiom p7 : A H ∧ (B H → (¬ E H ∧ ¬ B H))

theorem goal : S H ∧ (¬ E H ∨ (E H → F H)) := by
  have hA : A H := And.left p7
  have hB : B H := p1 H (And.intro p6 hA)
  have hNE : ¬ E H := And.left ((And.right p7) hB)
  exact And.intro p6 (Or.inl hNE)

axiom Restaurant : Type
axiom L : Restaurant → Prop
axiom N : Restaurant → Prop
axiom R : Restaurant → Prop
axiom T : Restaurant → Prop
axiom P : Restaurant → Prop
axiom h : Restaurant

-- Premises
axiom a1 : ∀ x : Restaurant, L x → ¬ N x
axiom a2 : ∀ x : Restaurant, R x → L x
axiom a3 : ∃ x : Restaurant, ¬ T x ∧ N x
axiom a4 : ∀ x : Restaurant, P x → R x
axiom a5 : R h ∨ P h

-- Goal: (T h ∧ N h) → (R h ∧ ¬ T h)
theorem goal : (T h ∧ N h) → (R h ∧ ¬ T h) := by
  -- Derive R h from a5 and a4
  have rh : R h := by
    cases a5 with
    | inl rh => exact rh
    | inr ph => exact a4 h ph
  -- From R h and a2, get L h; then from L h and a1, get ¬ N h
  have lh : L h := a2 h rh
  have notNh : ¬ N h := a1 h lh
  -- Now prove the implication
  intro hAss
  -- From N h and ¬ N h, get a contradiction
  have contra : False := notNh hAss.right
  -- From contradiction, get ¬ T h
  have notTh : ¬ T h := by
    intro _
    exact contra
  -- Conclude R h ∧ ¬ T h
  exact And.intro rh notTh

premises:
If something can transport multiple passengers, then they are not one-seaters.
All Tesla Model 3 can transport multiple passengers.
All single-seat electric cars are one-seaters.

axiom Car : Type
axiom J : Car

axiom SoloEV : Car → Prop
axiom SingleSeatEV : Car → Prop
axiom OneSeater : Car → Prop
axiom TeslaModel3 : Car → Prop
axiom CanTransportMultiplePassengers : Car → Prop

-- Contextual premises
axiom canMulti_imp_not_one : ∀ x : Car, CanTransportMultiplePassengers x → ¬ OneSeater x
axiom tesla3_imp_multi : ∀ x : Car, TeslaModel3 x → CanTransportMultiplePassengers x
axiom singleSeatEV_imp_one : ∀ x : Car, SingleSeatEV x → OneSeater x
axiom soloEV_imp_singleSeatEV : ∀ x : Car, SoloEV x → SingleSeatEV x
axiom J_not_tesla3_imp_or : ¬ TeslaModel3 J → (¬ TeslaModel3 J ∨ SingleSeatEV J)

-- Given fact from the question
axiom J_is_SoloEV : SoloEV J

-- Goal: John's car is a one-seater
theorem goal : OneSeater J := by
  have h1 : SingleSeatEV J := soloEV_imp_singleSeatEV J J_is_SoloEV
  exact singleSeatEV_imp_one J h1
